    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "> Again, connect* doesn't exist in v7, that's what could be made more clear in the migration script though. Thanks for your feedback!\r\n\r\nSorry you may say this but it is there. So I would check the code and make sure... on checking react-instantsearch v7.2.0 you in-fact export everything from core, so one would expect not to have to install core at all and use `react-instantsearch` only.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"698\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-10-18 at 12 44 26\" src=\"https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/assets/8969851/0c7002e2-56e9-4510-b5ff-b869b3249cd9\">\r\n\r\nthe below is a lot of connect functions considering they don't \"exist\" for v7 these functions are also **usable** but fail type checking.\r\n<img width=\"525\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-10-18 at 12 45 15\" src=\"https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/assets/8969851/ce0cdc43-d9f8-4a4b-8736-36c4b97ef98d\">\r\n\r\nthe below is your react-instantsearch-core types which indeed export connect* function type declarations\r\n<img width=\"1279\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-10-18 at 12 47 15\" src=\"https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/assets/8969851/7bc4c099-ff60-417f-be6e-910b7abb80a1\">\r\n\r\nSo I appreciate your intention is that they don't exist... but they very much do and make your docs a TON more confusing... at the least this is a bug and not expected behaviour on either my part as the consumer reading your docs and your part as you say they shouldn't exist at all in v7 😅 \r\n",
